{
  "local_port": 48900,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, Hollywood saw the release of numerous critically acclaimed films across various genres. Below is a list of some of the top-rated Hollywood movies from that year, based on critical reception, audience scores, and accolades:\n\n1. **Get Out**\n   - *Genre:* Horror/Thriller\n   - *Director:* Jordan Peele\n   - *Synopsis:* A young African-American man uncovers disturbing secrets when he meets his white girlfriend's family.\n   - *Highlights:* Praised for its social commentary, suspenseful storytelling, and Peele's direction.\n\n2. **Dunkirk**\n   - *Genre:* War/Drama\n   - *Director:* Christopher Nolan\n   - *Synopsis:* Portrays the harrowing evacuation of Allied soldiers from Dunkirk during World War II.\n   - *Highlights:* Noted for its immersive cinematography, minimal dialogue, and intense pacing.\n\n3. **Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri**\n   - *Genre:* Crime/Drama\n   - *Director:* Martin McDonagh\n   - *Synopsis:* A mother's quest for justice after her daughter's unsolved murder leads her to confront local authorities.\n   - *Highlights:* Strong performances, particularly by Frances McDormand and Sam Rockwell.\n\n4. **Lady Bird**\n   - *Genre:* Coming-of-Age/Drama\n   - *Director:* Greta Gerwig\n   - *Synopsis:* Follows a high school senior navigating her relationships, aspirations, and turbulent family life in Sacramento.\n   - *Highlights:* Celebrated for its authentic portrayal of adolescence and Gerwig's sharp writing.\n\n5. **The Shape of Water**\n   - *Genre:* Fantasy/Romance\n   - *Director:* Guillermo del Toro\n   - *Synopsis:* A mute janitor forms a unique bond with an amphibious creature held in a high-security laboratory.\n   - *Highlights:* Acclaimed for its imaginative storytelling, visual beauty, and emotional depth. Won the Academy Award for Best Picture.\n\n6. **Call Me by Your Name**\n   - *Genre:* Romance/Drama\n   - *Director:* Luca Guadagnino\n   - *Synopsis:* Explores the romantic relationship between a 17-year-old living in Italy and his father's American assistant.\n   - *Highlights:* Lauded for its sensitive performances and beautiful cinematography.\n\n7. **Blade Runner 2049**\n   - *Genre:* Science Fiction/Thriller\n   - *Director:* Denis Villeneuve\n   - *Synopsis:* A new blade runner unearths a long-buried secret that could plunge society into chaos.\n   - *Highlights:* Praised for its stunning visual effects, depth of storytelling, and faithful continuation of the original's legacy.\n\n8. **Logan**\n   - *Genre:* Superhero/Action\n   - *Director:* James Mangold\n   - *Synopsis:* An aging Wolverine cares for an ailing Professor X while protecting a young mutant from dark forces.\n   - *Highlights:* Commended for its mature, gritty take on the superhero genre and Hugh Jackman's performance.\n\n9. **The Post**\n   - *Genre:* Historical/Drama\n   - *Director:* Steven Spielberg\n   - *Synopsis:* Chronicles The Washington Post's role in publishing the Pentagon Papers, exposing government secrets.\n   - *Highlights:* Noted for its strong performances by Meryl Streep and Tom Hanks, and its timely themes on press freedom.\n\n10. **Coco**\n    - *Genre:* Animation/Adventure\n    - *Directors:* Lee Unkrich, Adrian Molina\n    - *Synopsis:* A young boy embarks on a journey to the Land of the Dead to discover his family's history.\n    - *Highlights:* Celebrated for its vibrant animation, heartfelt story, and cultural authenticity. Won the Academy Award for Best Animated Feature.\n\n11. **War for the Planet of the Apes**\n    - *Genre:* Science Fiction/Drama\n    - *Director:* Matt Reeves\n    - *Synopsis:* Follows Caesar and his fellow apes as they navigate conflict with a ruthless human army.\n    - *Highlights:* Applauded for its emotional depth, visual effects, and compelling performances by the cast of motion-capture actors.\n\n12. **It**\n    - *Genre:* Horror\n    - *Director:* Andy Muschietti\n    - *Synopsis:* A group of children confronts a malevolent entity that emerges from the sewers of their hometown every 27 years.\n    - *Highlights:* Successful adaptation of Stephen King's novel, praised for its atmosphere and performances, especially by Bill Skarsg\u00e5rd as Pennywise.\n\n13. **Wonder Woman**\n    - *Genre:* Superhero/Action\n    - *Director:* Patty Jenkins\n    - *Synopsis:* Diana Prince leaves her sheltered island to fight in World War I, discovering her full powers and destiny.\n    - *Highlights:* Celebrated as a groundbreaking film for its female-led superhero narrative and empowering themes.\n\n14. **Thor: Ragnarok**\n    - *Genre:* Superhero/Action\n    - *Director:* Taika Waititi\n    - *Synopsis:* Thor teams up with the Hulk and other allies to prevent the destruction of Asgard.\n    - *Highlights:* Praised for its humor, vibrant style, and fresh take on the Thor franchise.\n\n15. **Baby Driver**\n    - *Genre:* Action/Crime\n    - *Director:* Edgar Wright\n    - *Synopsis:* A young getaway driver seeks freedom from a life of crime through his passion for music.\n    - *Highlights:* Noted for its tight choreography of action sequences synchronized with an eclectic soundtrack.\n\nThese films garnered significant attention and acclaim in 2017, each contributing uniquely to their respective genres. Depending on your interests\u2014be it thought-provoking drama, thrilling action, or heartfelt storytelling\u20142017 offered a diverse array of high-quality Hollywood movies.",
